{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2018}} {{short description|2017 creationist documentary film}} {{Infobox film | name = Is Genesis History? | image = Is Genesis History film poster.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = Theatrical release poster | director = Thomas Purifoy Jr. | producer = Thomas Purifoy Jr. | writer = Thomas Purifoy Jr. | starring = {{Plainlist| * [[George Grant (author)|George Grant]] * [[Paul Nelson (creationist)|Paul Nelson]] * [[Marcus R. Ross]] * [[Andrew A. Snelling]] * [[Kurt Wise]] }} | released = {{Film date|2017|2|23}} | runtime = 100 minutes<ref name="BOM" /> | country = United States | distributor = [[Fathom Events]] | budget = | gross = $2.6&nbsp;million<ref name="TheNumbers">{{cite web | title = Is Genesis History? (2017) | url = http://www.the-numbers.com/movie/Is-Genesis-History#tab=summary | publisher = [[The Numbers (website)|The Numbers]] | accessdate = September 30, 2017 }}</ref> }}
'''''Is Genesis History?''''' is a 2017 American [[Christian film industry|Christian film]] that uses [[creation science]], a [[pseudoscientific]] concept, to promote [[Young Earth creationism|Young Earth creationist]] beliefs that contradict established [[scientific fact]]s regarding the [[Big Bang|origin of the Universe]], the [[age of the Earth]], and the [[common descent]] of all lifeforms.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thenaturalhistorian.com/2017/06/26/is-genesis-history-digging-for-truth-and-coming-up-empty-handed-3/|title=Is Genesis History: Digging for Truth and Coming up Empty-Handed|last=Cade|first=Lars|date=June 26, 2017|website=Naturalis Historia|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title = IAP Statement on the Teaching of Evolution | accessdate = June 3, 2018 | url = http://www.interacademies.org/10878/13901.aspx }}</ref><ref>{{cite book | title = The Philosophy of Science – An Encyclopedia | year = 2006 | publisher = Psychology Press (Routledge) | isbn = 978-0-415-93927-0 | editor1-first = Sahotra | editor1-last = Sarkar | editor2-first = Jessica | editor2-last = Pfeifer | location = Problem of demarcation | pages = 192, 194-195 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=od68ge7aF6wC&pg=PA194 }}</ref>
The film was written, directed, and produced by Thomas Purifoy Jr., who said he was inspired to make it after his daughter watched the [[Bill Nye–Ken Ham debate]] in 2014 and began asking him questions about the [[creation–evolution controversy]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.nwaonline.com/news/2017/feb/18/daughter-s-queries-prompted-genesis-fil-1/ | title = Daughter's Queries Prompted Genesis Film | last1 = Storm | first1 = Christie | date = February 18, 2017 | work = [[Arkansas Democrat-Gazette]] | accessdate = March 26, 2017 }}</ref> Del Tackett, the creator of [[Focus on the Family]]'s "The Truth Project", narrates the film.<ref name=CP2017 /><ref name="fraser">{{cite web | last1 = Fraser | first1 = Trevor | title = Movie Musings: Genesis, Leon Russell and More | url = http://www.orlandosentinel.com/entertainment/os-movie-musings-is-genesis-history-0216-story.html | date = February 16, 2017 | work = [[Orlando Sentinel]] | accessdate = April 12, 2017 }}</ref> Interviewing thirteen creationists, the narrator of the film argues that [[Genesis creation narrative|Genesis]] portrays real historical events.<ref name=CP2017>{{cite web | last1 = Law | first1 = Jeannie | title = Evidence of Young Earth Creationism Will Debunk Current Scientific Paradigm, Filmmaker Says | url = http://www.christianpost.com/news/evidence-of-young-earth-creationism-will-debunk-current-scientific-paradigm-filmmaker-says-175074/ | date = February 16, 2017 | work = [[The Christian Post]] | accessdate = March 26, 2017 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | last1 = Tomlin | first1 = Gregory | title = ''Is Genesis History?'' Film Aims to Answer Questions of Creation, Evolution, Global Flood | url = http://christianexaminer.com/article/is-genesis-history-film-aims-to-answer-questions-of-creation-evolution-global-flood/51252.htm | date = November 29, 2016 | publisher = [[Christian Examiner (California)|Christian Examiner]] | accessdate = March 26, 2017 }}</ref> Other speakers include [[George Grant (author)|George Grant]], [[Paul Nelson (creationist)|Paul Nelson]], [[Marcus R. Ross]], [[Andrew A. Snelling]], and [[Kurt Wise]], as well as [[Larry Vardiman]] in the film's bonus features.
''Is Genesis History?'' was released into American theaters on Thursday, February 23, 2017.<ref name="BOM">{{Mojo title |id=isgenesishistory |title=Is Genesis History? |accessdate=August 22, 2017}}</ref> It was shown in 704 theaters and grossed $1,796,182 in one night.<ref name="BOM" /> Over 143,000 people saw the film that night, and its box office earnings were the highest of any film in theaters in the United States that night.<ref>{{Cite news | last1 = Guerrasio | first1 = Jason | url = http://www.businessinsider.com/faith-based-movies-in-trump-era-2017-4 | title = How religious movies are thriving more than ever before under Trump | work = Business Insider | date = April 5, 2017 | access-date = September 3, 2017 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170903121016/http://www.businessinsider.com/faith-based-movies-in-trump-era-2017-4 | archive-date = September 3, 2017 | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="LawCP">{{cite web | last1 = Law | first1 = Jeannie | title = 'Is Genesis History?' Film on Young Earth Creationism Returns to Theaters for Encore Screening | url = http://www.christianpost.com/news/is-genesis-history-film-on-young-earth-creationism-returns-to-theaters-for-encore-screening-176559/ | date = March 4, 2017 | work = [[The Christian Post]] | accessdate = August 22, 2017 }}</ref><ref name="AMFM">{{cite web | title = Is Genesis History? Fathom Event Hits No. 1 in Box Office, Returns to Theaters March 2nd and 7th | url = http://www.amfm-magazine.com/is-genesis-history-one-night-only-fathom-event-hits-1-in-box-office-returns-to-theaters-march-2nd-and-7th/ | date = February 27, 2017 | publisher = AMFM Magazine | accessdate = August 22, 2017 }}</ref> The film was shown again in theaters on March 2 and 7, 2017 in the United States,<ref name="LawCP" /><ref name="AMFM" /> as well as in Canada on March 14, 2017. The film went on to earn a total box office of $2,570,355, after the encore showings.<ref name="TheNumbers" /> The film was re-released in around 850 theaters for an anniversary showing on February 22, 2018, with a bonus scene of [[Wheaton College (Illinois)|Wheaton College]] students touring the [[Ark Encounter]], a creationist attraction operated by [[Answers in Genesis]]. The students were members of a creationist club which had requested a screening of the film, leading to controversy among the Christian school's faculty, nearly all of whom reject the "historical creationism" that ''Is Genesis History?'' presents.<ref name=CP2018>{{cite web | last1 = Showalter | first1 = Brandon | title = Young Earth Creationist, Wheaton College Students Speak at 1-Y Anniv. Release of 'Is Genesis History?' | url = https://www.christianpost.com/news/young-earth-creationist-wheaton-college-students-speak-at-1-year-anniversary-release-is-genesis-history-218669/ | date = February 21, 2018 | work = [[The Christian Post]] | accessdate = March 7, 2018 }}</ref>
