The '''Kingdom of EnenKio''' is a falsely claimed [[micronation]] near the [[Marshall Islands]] run by Robert Moore.<ref name=quakio>{{cite web|url=http://www.quatloos.com/enenkio.htm |title=The Kingdom of Enen Kio |work=[[Quatloos!]]}}</ref>
The [[Republic of the Marshall Islands]] has claimed [[Wake Island]], which it calls "Enen-Kio". In 1973, Marshallese lawmakers meeting in Saipan at the Congress of Micronesia, the legislative body for the [[Trust Territory of the Pacific Islands]], asserted that "Enen-Kio is and always has been the property of the people of the Marshall Islands." Their claim was based on oral legends and songs.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/3864881/wake_island_claimed_by_marshall_islands/ |title=Wake Island Claimed By Marshall Islanders |work=The Cameron Herald |date=8 February 1973 |page=2}}</ref> "EnenKio" means "Island of the orange flower" and comes from the small orange flower that is native to the island.<ref>{{cite journal |url=https://books.google.com/?id=RzsTAQAAIAAJ&dq=enenkio&q=%22Island+of+the+orange+flower%22 |title=Enen-kio: Island of the Kio Flower |journal=Micronesian Reporter |publisher=Public Information Office, Trust Territory of the Pacific Islands |volume=19 |date=1971 |page=34}}</ref>
The self-declared Kingdom of EnenKio has also claimed Wake Island as a separate sovereign nation and has issued [[passport]]s.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.theaustralian.com.au/news/inquirer/walking-on-eggshells/news-story/e0f800a86f936c67291189541046737c |title=Walking on eggshells |work=[[The Australian]] |date=28 February 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://archives.digitaltoday.in/indiatoday/20020930/cyber.html |title=Con Countries |work=[[India Today]] |date=30 September 2002}}</ref> The Kingdom of EnenKio is not recognized in any international forum as a sovereign state, nor does any internationally recognized state recognize it. In 1997 the [[Dominion of Melchizedek]], a micronation engaged in financial fraud, reported that the two had entered into relations.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Rf_mHK98RNwC&pg=PA116 |title=Global Pirates: Fraud in the Offshore Insurance Industry |author=Robert Tillman |year=2002 |publisher=[[Northeastern University Press]] |isbn=978-1-55553-505-6 |page=116}}</ref> The Kingdom of EnenKio is characterized as a scam by anti-fraud website [[Quatloos!]]<ref name=quakio /> In 2000, Robert Moore, who claimed to be the head of state, was prevented by the [[U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission]] from fraudulently issuing bonds for the non-existent nation.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sec.gov/litigation/litreleases/lr16780.htm |title=SECURITIES AND EXCHANGE COMMISSION v. Robert F. Moore |work=[[U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission]] |date=26 October 2000}}</ref>
On 23 April 1998 the Marshall Islands government issued Circular Note 01-98, which vigorously denied the Kingdom of EnenKio and the Dominion of Melchizedek's claims:
{{quote box|align=right|width=25%|bgcolor=#c6dbf7|quote="The Government of the Republic of the Marshall Islands condemns the claims and activities asserted by representatives of the "Kingdom of EnenKio" and the "Dominion of Melchizedek". The representatives making claims of separate sovereignty are not citizens of the Republic of the Marshall Islands and have no right to make claims on behalf of Marshallese landowners. Furthermore, these representatives are making fraudulent assertions that violate the Republic of the Marshall Islands' constitution. The area of land and ocean which the "Kingdom of EnenKio" asserts as a sovereign nation separate from the Marshall Islands and the area of land and ocean which the "Dominion of Melchizedek" is asserting control over are areas within the geographical and political boundaries of the Republic of the Marshall Islands.
The Government of the Republic of the Marshall Islands discourages all independent sovereign nations having diplomatic relations with the Republic from acknowledging any fraudulent claims made by representatives of the "Kingdom of EnenKio" and the "Dominion of Melchizedek". |author=Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Republic of the Marshall Islands<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.quatloos.com/marshall_islands_declares.htm |title=Marshall Islands Ministry of Foreign Affairs Declares "Kingdom of EnenKio" a Fraud |website=[[Quatloos!]]}}</ref>}}
